cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with analyzing videos of human activities and discovering motion primitives from them. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper mentions applications in human-robot interaction and learning by demonstration. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses a non-parametric Bayes mixture model for unsupervised clustering of motion primitives. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper deals with recognizing and categorizing human motion. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is relevant as the paper mentions applications in intuitive human-robot interaction and human behavior analysis.
